# AINotes — GitHub Repo Reader

## Project purpose

Personal knowledge base for reading and annotating GitHub repositories. One folder per repo; all notes in Markdown.

## Structure

```
ainote/
├── CLAUDE.md           # Project instructions (legacy; mirrored in .cursor/rules)
├── README.md           # Reading list — index of all tracked repos
└── <owner>-<repo>/     # One folder per GitHub repo
    ├── overview.md     # Summary, purpose, key concepts
    ├── architecture.md # Code structure, modules, design patterns
    └── notes.md        # Personal reading notes, questions, highlights
```

## Conventions

- Folder naming: `<github-owner>-<repo-name>` (lowercase, hyphens).
- Root `README.md` is the reading list — link to each repo folder.
- Content only in `.md` files.
- Each repo folder must have at least `overview.md`.

## Workflow

1. New repo: create `<owner>-<repo>/overview.md` and add an entry to `README.md`.
2. Ongoing notes: `notes.md` inside the repo folder.
3. Architecture: document in `architecture.md`.

## Agent guidance

- Default language for replies and note writing: **Chinese (Simplified)**.
- When adding a repo, always update `README.md` with a link to the new folder.
- Keep notes factual and tied to actual source code.
- Use headings, fenced code blocks, and links to specific files/lines when possible.
- Do not create files outside this structure without asking the user.
